[Level 10 Achievement Bonus] Mode: Fortu has been unlocked!
You can now evade erotic attacks!

[Level 20 Achievement Bonus] Skill: Counter has been
unlocked! You can now return the damage you just received!

[Level 30 Achievement Bonus] Skill: All-Green has been
unlocked! You can fully recover your vitals while reducing
restraint by one level!

[Level 40 Achievement Bonus] Mode: Deus has been unlocked!
It consumes energy every turn, but all abilities are
enhanced!

[Level 51 Achievement Bonus] Skill: Metaburst has been
unlocked! Consumes bullets and energy to deal massive damage
while escaping restraints!

[Max Vital Achievement Bonus] The amount healed by Self
Repair has increased!

[Max Energy Achievement Bonus] Energy consumption in Mode
Deus has been reduced to 10!

[Max Attack Achievement Bonus] The power of Power Knuckle
has increased!

[Max Ammo Achievement Bonus] The power of attacks that
consume bullets has increased!

[Max Smoke Achievement Bonus] Evasion rate in Mode Fortu has
increased!
All Grow Cores have been used.

\n<Marion>I let my guard down after defeating the primordial monster.
The number of monsters hasn't decreased at all.

\n<Marion>Makina is working hard too, but... at this rate, the two of
us will die from overwork.

\n<Marion>Answer my question. Who are you? I'm busy and haven't slept,
so I'm irritable and ready to knock someone out.

\n<Marion>Wow!! Could it be financial support!? Sorry for being harsh
earlier!

\n<President>Ah, no, don't worry about it. I apologize for visiting so
suddenly.

\n<President>I got permission from your assistant named Syst to enter
here specially.

\n<Marion>That's presumptuous of them. So, what does the big-shot
corporate president want?
\n<President>Let me get straight to the point.
\n<President>\C[2]Could you turn my daughter into a modified girl?

\n<President>My daughter was injured by a monster. You've turned someone
into a modified girl before, haven't you?

\n<Marion>This isn't a hospital. And casually turning someone into a
modified girl is dangerous.

\n<Marion>Can she fight to the death like Makina? It's not something a
parent can decide on their own whim.
\n<President>It's her own wish. \C[27]Eury\C[0] admires Makina, you see.

\n<President>Yes. She's dreamed of becoming a hero since she was little,
just like a boy.

\n<President>Dr. Marion, please. I'll pay whatever it takes. I want to
make her dream come true.

\n<Marion>(...This is crazy. It's not something to be agreed upon
lightly.)

\n<Marion>(But if there was another modified girl, it might make our
work a bit easier?)

\n<Marion>(I never thought about increasing the number of modified
girls because I didn't think anyone would want to risk their
life to fight evil...)

\n<Marion>What you're asking for is unreasonable. To be blunt, it's
dangerous.
\n<Marion>But it's an idea that could benefit everyone.

\n<Marion>We're short-handed in fighting monsters with just Makina.
Having more modified girls is a good thing.

\n<Marion>...But are you really okay with it? She could be killed by
monsters out of the blue one day.

\n<Marion>Being killed is still better than what worse things could
happen to her.

\n<President>...Honestly, I can't say I would be able to endure that
moment.
\n<President>But still, I want to make Eury's dream come true.

\n<President>She will definitely become a strong modified girl and
contribute to this world.

\n<President>...Next time, I'll bring Eury along. Can we make the final
decision then?
\n<Marion>Sorry, but I'm busy. I can't talk for long.
\n<President>Dr. Marion, thank you for your valuable time.

\n<Eury>It's the \v[224] day since I've come to Tengeki Street.
Let's do our best today too!
